cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to classify wound images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks also suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a likely sub-category. The mobile application frontend for tracking wound recovery suggests human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of smartphones, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) as they are often used for capturing and sharing visual media.
